Type.Name: CodeGenerator

TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi abstract beforefieldinit CodeGenerator extends System.Object implements class System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeGenerator

Type.ThreadSafetyStatement: Gtk# is thread aware, but not thread safe; See the <link location="node:gtk-sharp/programming/threads">Gtk# Thread Programming</link> for details.

remarks.para: This is a useful base class for code generators to derive from. Code generators are capable of rendering source code in a specific language according to the structure of a Code Document Object Model (CodeDOM) graph. This class provides many functions and methods to generate specific types of code from a CodeDOM graph.

block.para: This class contains a link demand and an inheritance demand at the class level that applies to all members. A is thrown when either the immediate caller or the derived class does not have full-trust permission. For details about security demands, see Link Demands and Inheritance Demands.

summary.para: Provides an example implementation of the interface. This class is abstract.

.method familyhidebysig newslot virtual instance string CreateEscapedIdentifier(string value) cil managed

remarks.para: tests whether the identifier conflicts with reserved or language keywords, and if so, returns an equivalent name with language-specific escape code formatting. The returned name is referred to an escaped identifier. The escaped identifier contains the same but includes escape code formatting to differentiate it from conflicting keywords. For example, could be preceded by an at sign ("@") or delimited by square brackets ("[" and "]") to create an escaped identifier.

block.para: The default implementation of this method does nothing.

summary.para: Creates an escaped identifier for the specified value.

returns.para: The escaped identifier for the value.

Docs.param: The string to create an escaped identifier for.

MemberSignature.Value: protected abstract string CreateValidIdentifier (string value);
.method familyhidebysig newslot virtual instance string CreateValidIdentifier(string value) cil managed

remarks.para: tests whether the identifier conflicts with reserved or language keywords, and if so, returns a valid identifier name that does not conflict. The returned identifier contains the same but includes escape code formatting to differentiate it from conflicting keywords. Typically, if the value requires modification, it is preceded by an underscore "_".

block.para: The default implementation of this method does nothing.

summary.para: Creates a valid identifier for the specified value.

returns.para: A valid identifier for the value.

Docs.param: A string to create a valid identifier for.

remarks.para: Code for members is generated differently depending on the context. For example, code for methods on an interface or fields on an enumeration is generated differently from code for the same member on a class. This implementation assumes that the member is being generated for the class context.

remarks.para: It is possible for the identifier fields of objects to contain field escape characters and hidden code which can allow security violations. This method checks the literal fields of each in a tree for characters which could be used to hide code, and throws an exception if an identifier field contains an invalid character.
This method calls the method to validate each identifier in the specified or tree, and throws an exception if an identifier is invalid or contains invalid characters.

Call this method and pass it the containing the code graph to generate before generating code to block the use of certain character sequences that can be used to include hidden code within an identifier field. This method is not called automatically by any generate code methods.
